cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the evaluation of the performance of UAV-aided networks with mmWave communications, which involves information transmission and processing. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on the communication process between UAVs and ground stations, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a unified framework for evaluating the performance of UAV-aided networks, which involves the design and analysis of control systems. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the data rate and transmission quality of UAV-aided networks, which are relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems): The paper considers the cooperative transmission between UAVs and ground stations, which can be viewed as a multi-agent system.
